{
  "stem": "4963.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember that when my cousin used to go to work, everyone had big-- like, big pockets, like a basket-- well, it wasn't a basket.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a clothes-- like a laundry, clothes bag under your clothes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And your clothes was really designed specially for that to hide that-- that bag.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in the bag, they would place, you know, food, bread, and butter-- you know, staples to eat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So that-- various scenes like this I really remember very distinctly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now my uncle, as I mentioned, we-- we really-- we were really almost, I would say, privileged.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My uncle would go to the-- to the committee.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was a Jewish committee that was appointed right away, and the Germans and the Lithuanians would work with the Jewish committee.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, my uncle was part of the committee.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was really like a dog-eat-dog life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean everyone was out for himself, for his family and for himself, to-- for survival.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When it comes right down to it, I really felt that, you know, that you do what you have to do for survival.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And even if you-- it means putting the other person in danger, as long as you survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw that in the ghetto and even to the point where-- where I suppose the Germans were forcing some of the committee members to-- to, as we call them, [? masser, ?] which means to tell on another person, as to who was-- who was bringing in lots of food.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because if they-- if the committee people or the police-- we had our own Jewish police as well-- so if the police did not enforce it and did not tell the Germans, then they would get the beating and their lives would be in danger.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
